<br>
With regard to the time that AD were in SF camping RF - I can confirm that this was started sometime on Sunday as stated, as late on Sunday afternoon (bearing in mind we are GMT) Pooks first mentioned to me that Alderac was doing RF and he had sent him our best wishes.  Throughout his camp we sent him well wishes whenever we were online - and everytime we checked he was STILL in SF.  So as to all the confusion about exact time - I hope this clarifies this matter up.  <br>
<br>
Personally, after 3 days without sleep on my 5th and luckily last RF camp, I couldn't even tell you what day it was let alone how long I had been there - and I know that this was true for other people who had camped the duration with me.  Heck if he hadn't spawned when he did I am pretty sure I would have started thinking the computer was talking to me or something... Lack of sleep does that to you - it makes you quicker to anger and less aware of time passing.  Well it does me, I don't know about you all.<br>
<br>
As is probably aware my last camp was quite a nasty one - yes we rolled and luckily we won, but it doesn't alter the fact that a kind of agreement had been made but there was the ever present threat that he would be KS'd from us.  This is ALWAYS in the back of the clerics mind throughout this camp.  When the guild you have rolled against and won turns up again (Thank you Anlah'Shok - I only ever had well wishes from you guys after the roll) you wonder in the back of your mind are they deciding to renege (sp.) on the deal and take the kill after all.  That may not be their intention but you sure as hell think it.<br>
<br>
The server is obviously split over whether this is a camp or a FFA - whichever side of the fence you are on, courtesy and politeness should not be forgotten.  I personally was told in tells that I was being rude for not agreeing to roll on the camp after another guild walked into the camp - and this continued for a while (another point being it was NOT the cleric who wanted RF either).  Personally I chose not to talk to anyone other than the clerics involved while there - this may be a good course of action to be honest.  Tempers are heated and things are said in the moment.  I know things were by ALL parties at my RF camp.<br>
<br>
With regard to the comments that the camp would be respected IF there was force there capable of taking RF.... At no time has it ever been in disagreement that AD had a raid force there throughout the camp.  Therefore, why am I constantly seeing that &quot;IF they had a raid force there we would have respected the camp&quot; when it quite clearly was not.  If you feel it is a FFA stick to your guns and stick up for your convictions as Raijin did (which I respect although I do not personally agree with him) - there is no right or wrong side to this camp - just personal opinion.  As for not respecting being walking in and saying &quot;@#%$ you&quot; and killing him the moment he popped - well that is what happened to me on my 4th camp and to a dear friend just last night (who's guild were there in force and about to engage) and just brings forth the whole messy nature of this camp.<br>
<br>
I personally do not ever feel that this matter of RF will be sorted, mainly due to the fact that some people on our server have little or no respect for other players.  Maybe they think that there is no-one behind those characters - think again.  Every single person that is KS'd from RF, Raster or whichever camp feels the disappointment and upset.  All we can hope is that we do not lower ourselves down to their level or as was said earlier, what would this server become!  I certainly know that it would no longer be a place I would care to spend time in a game that I should enjoy playing.<br>
<br>
On another note - yes the epic is of use in raids (invaluable if you will when wiped out by AoW for example - still laughing bout that one - Sorry Rimm) but more importantly, my epic means that I can instantly res people. I feel that I am like the vast majority of clerics on our server - I do a /who all &quot;PlayerX&quot; when I see a corpse that has a res timer on it and shoot them a tell asking if they want a res.  No donations accepted nor expected.  This is what my epic means to me.  No wasting of mana or having to mem spell - send the tell and res inc.  Nice and easy and appreciated by the player you res (well almost always - there are always those that expect it and also expect you to stand and cast Aego on them and their group because you can).<br>
<br>
I am really sorry you didn't get RF Alderac - you are one of the good guys and really deserved to get him (and no I am not saying the other cleric did not deserve their epic before I get jumped on).  All I can say is that it is worth it in the long run and yes, epic the correct word for it - I added 20 played days on Smilin to get mine (but then I was unlucky on a lot of the spawns).<br>
<br>
Well that is my 2cp on a subject I, along with a LOT of clerics and their friends, feel strongly on.<br>
<br>
Smilin<br>
High Priestess of Bristlebane<br>
