  <p><center> <IMG SRC="http://web.tampabay.rr.com/staticpulse/Velondra.jpg"> <br>60th Ranger<br>Proud Dragon Bait of Phoenix Crusaders <br>Beloved of Neijek Domisilva </img> </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uthanozdetroll.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThanozDeTroll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/30/02 7:58:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3495.topic&index=214>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bloodwolfe</span><hr size=1> Bloodwolfe, I have to applaud you.  That was a classy post, and I salute you.<br>
<br>
I am only one elder in PC so I can only speak for myself, though I honestly believe I am echoing the sentiments of others who will likely post here in a similar vein in the coming hours.<br>
<br>
None of us has relished the attention this episode has gotten, nor do I think any of the parties involved believed what they did was ethically in the wrong.  The point is, though, that nothing can be changed unless we all learn from what has transpired.  And, I believe, many involved on all sides have learned a great deal so that chances of these parties being involved in this again will be greatly reduced.  (Will this type of event happen again over RF?...Heck, yeah, I can guarantee you it will...probably on the very next spawn..but I bet you won't see these 3 guilds snapping at each other over it. LOL) Actions, however rightly conceived, can have drastic side effects that none ever imagined, and this was probably one such instance where that was proven true.  <br>
<br>
There has been a lot of talk on these boards about PC having lost its honor.  There have also been a lot of attacks from players who either left PC or were removed from our guild.  It is easy to bash and complain about a problem when you are not actively trying or care enough to be part of the solution, I guess.  I realize it is easy to think that they be right, and I can only refute their positions with this:  <br>
<br>
The PC internal channels have been full of nothing but talk about this since it first came up....what we did right, what we did wrong, what the other guilds did pro and con....how we could have done better, how we can avoid it in the future...and of course, many discussions about the different perspectives the server has overall with regard to RF.  All I can ask is that you consider IF PC is now so corrupt and bereft of honor, why have we been so dealing so intently and internally with these issues instead of gloating or posting &quot;in your face&quot; messages that some seem to have anticipated?<br>
<br>
Why?  Because the honor is not dead and it will never be, regardless of what some individuals may baselessly believe.   Yes, our numbers have swelled over the past few months, and yes, some bad decisions have been made in the heat of the moment.  Yes, we've had to eat some crow that we didn't particularly enjoy.  I know I am sorry some of these things have happened, and I know others are, too.  But honestly, guys...rants to the point of hysterics are generally not an effective way to make your point.  I don't think there is any one person or any one organization out there that can say they have always done everything right FOR EVERYONE the first time and everytime thereafter. <br>
<br>
Being PC still remains a great honor for those of us in the guild, just as being AD or GL remains a great honor for you in those guilds.  Mutual in game respect is as important as it has ever been and I suspect that those watch the game closely (rather than these boards) will see developments that will bear this out.<br>
<br>
In closing, I just want to say again that I think your post was a great one, Bloodwolfe, and I thank you for it.  Regardless of what has been said by those outside our guild, know that PC is listening to you and admires the leadership you have shown.  Hopefully, we will meet on the field again one day soon and you will have similar feelings for us.<br>
<br>
Thanoz &quot;not so dumb for a troll&quot; Krackjaw <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=164771>My Magelo</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udakawaka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daka Waka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/02 9:44:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3495.topic&index=215>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bloodwolfe</span><hr size=1> Bloodwolfe, That was a very refreshing post to see. I applaud you as well.<br>
